<H3> <TI>   Deng Xiaoping in `Intensive Care' at Military Hospital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deng Xiaoping in `Intensive Care' at Military Hospital </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Daughter Says Deng `Well,' `Resting' </H4>

<F P=102> HK2804033094 Hong Kong AFP in English 0326 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK2804033094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 28 (AFP) -- The daughter of China's 
paramount leader Deng Xiaoping Thursday denied rumours that her 
father's health was deteriorating, saying that he was well and 
resting at home. 
  "My father is at home in Beijing and his state of health has 
not changed," Deng Lin told AFP at a fashion show here organised 
by top French designer Pierre Cardin. 

</TEXT>

