<H3> <TI>   Fujian Elects New Governor Chen Mingyi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian Elects New Governor Chen Mingyi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704131594 Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The seven-day Second Session of the Seventh Fujian 
People's Congress ended in Fuzhou this morning after fulfilling 
various items listed on the agenda. The session called on 
people throughout the province to unite more closely around the 
CPC Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin as the core. 
Under the guidance of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of 
building socialism with Chinese characteristics and of the 
party's basic line, and under the leadership of the provincial 
party committee, they must be of one heart and one mind, and 
must make persistent efforts to carry out reform, rely on their 
own efforts, and work hard to promote their undertakings. They 
must strive for a new victory in our province's reform, opening 
up, and construction. 
  The executive chairmen of the session--Jia Qinglin, Yuan 
Qitong, Guo Ruiren, Huang Changxi, Su Changpei, Liu Yongye, 
Zhang Mingjun, Hong Huasheng, and Song Jun--were seated in the 
front rows of the rostrum. Presided over by Su Changpei, the 
session adopted a resolution approving the work report of the 
provincial people's government. The resolution held that the 
review of the report on last year's work conformed with reality, 
and that the tasks and arrangements proposed by the report for 
the coming year were practical and feasible. 
  The session also adopted the following resolutions: The 
resolution on the implementation of the plan for the national 
economic and social development in our province last year, and 
plan for this year; the resolution on our province's final 
accounts last year, and this year's budget; the resolution on 
the work report of the provincial people's congress standing 
committee; the resolution on the work report of the provincial 
higher people's court; and the resolution on the work report of 
the provincial people's procuratorate. 
  After approving these resolutions, Jia Qinglin, newly 
elected 
chairman of the provincial people's congress standing committee, 
and Chen Mingyi, newly elected governor of the provincial 
people's government, made their respective speeches. 

</TEXT>

