<DOCNO> FBIS4-4065 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi082_o_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-082 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai To Open Wholesale Business to Foreigners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai To Open Wholesale Business to Foreigners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2804084194 Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO in Chinese 8 Apr 94 p 21 </F>
<F P=103> HK2804084194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong LIEN HO PAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Special dispatch": "Foreign Firms Allowed To Engage in </F>
Wholesale Business and Set Up Foreign Trade Companies in 
Shanghai"] 
  [Text] Shanghai, 7 Apr (LIEN HO PAO)--Shanghai recently 
decided to allow foreign firms to engage in wholesale business 
and to set up foreign trade companies. The adoption of this 
policy will not only mark a major reform step in the opening of 
the mainland's tertiary industry, but will also greatly promote 
development in the Chang Jiang Valley. 
  Reportedly, the details of the scheme for implementing the 
decision are being formulated intensively. 
  In the course of expanding the scope of using foreign funds, 
apart from opening wholesale business, foreign trade, and retail 
sales of producer goods to foreign companies, Shanghai will also 
allow mainland retailers to launch joint ventures and carry out 
cooperation with foreign chain stores. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

