<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Releases Grain Reserves To Control Prices </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangdong Releases Grain Reserves To Control Prices </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704151894 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0948 GMT 
27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, April 27 (CNS)--The Guangdong provincial 
government has decided to make 50 million kilograms of reserved 
grain available in the market in order to keep the price under 
control and to make room for storage of summer grain crop. 
  The Guangdong government has since late last year 
implemented 
the instruction given by the state to stabilize grain and oil 
prices to guarantee supply which was generally in a stablestate 
across the province. The grain stock was so abundant that the 
price was kept at about RMB [renminbi] 100 for every 50 
kilograms of rice. As now is a time when the rural grain supply 
is temporarily in short supply and the summer grain crop is 
about to be put into storage, the provincial government decided 
to fill the market with 50 million kilograms of reserved grain 
to ensure an adequate food supply while 250 million kilograms of 
grain allocated by the state to the province isalso in place in 
the market. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

