<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Investment, Trade Flourish in Guangzhou </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Investment, Trade Flourish in Guangzhou </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704143994 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 0400 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou's foreign-related economy and foreign 
trade have been developing in a healthy way. By the end of 
March this year, another group of 699 contracts, using foreign 
capital valued at $3.38 billion, had been signed throughout the 
city, an increase 4.6 percent over the same period last year. 
In addition, foreign capital totalling $489 million actually 
had been used, 80.8 percent more than in the same period last 
year. The city's export volume reached $820 million, 
registering a 23 percent increase over the corresponding period 
last year. 
  Last year, the development of Guangzhou's foreign-related 
economy and foreign trade were marked by the following five main 
features: 1) The actual amount of invested capital increased by 
a greater margin owing to direct investment by foreign 
businessmen; 2) The scale of investment was larger and the 
quality of investment projects was higher; 3) The areas in which 
foreign businessmen made direct investments achieved diversified 
development; 4) There was a smooth transition of foreign trade 
and export to a new system, and a faster increase in exports, 
changing the previous situation of insufficient exports at the 
beginning of the year, and excessive increases at the end of the 
year; 5) New progress was made in opening up a diversified 
market. During the first quarter, Guangzhou examined and 
approved the establishment of three enterprises from abroad, and 
six enterprises were registered. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

