<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Residents' Income Levels Assessed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangdong Residents' Income Levels Assessed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704152194 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to statistics released recently by the 
provincial statistics bureau, the living expenditure income of 
the province's urban population ranked first among the nine 
coastal provinces and cities, including Beijing, Shanghai, and 
Tianjin. In terms of [words indistinct], although city dwellers 
in the province had an average per capita net income of 4,240 
yuan or so this year, ranking first among the nine provinces and 
cities, they spent a very large portion of their income, with 
average per capita spending 71 percent higher than the average 
level among the nine provinces and cities. Overall, the living 
expenditure level of the province's urban population belongs to 
an intermediate one in the nine provinces and cities. 
  The rumor that city dwellers in Guangdong have the highest 
consumption level in the country is not a fact. It is said that 
Guangdong's relatively high price levels have to do with this 
phenomenon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

