<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangzhou Cracks Down on Sale of Fake Commodities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangzhou Cracks Down on Sale of Fake Commodities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704144894 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0734 GMT 
27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, April 27 (CNS)--Guangzhou, capital of 
Guangdong Province, made sound achievements in fighting against 
fake and inferior-quality commodities in the first quarter this 
year with 203 cases of this kind being investigated and 136 of 
them being dealt with fines totalling RMB 1.11 million 
[renminbi]. 
  Relevant departments in the municipality have strengthened 
their efforts through their concerted coordination in cracking 
down on dens producing and selling such commodities. Some 3 000 
policemen and personnel from supervision and management 
departments have been involved in the campaign with a variety of 
goods with a face value of RMB 1.36 million including 
foodstuffs, cigarettes, wine, garments, household electrical 
appliances and compact discs being confiscated while on eight 
occasions destruction of such commodities have been held 
publicly and 18 exhibitions of such commodities have been 
staged. In addition, nearly 30 000 leaflets have been printed 
and distributed, greatly promoting the crack down. 

</TEXT>

