<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hainan Governor Meets ROK Assembly Committee Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hainan Governor Meets ROK Assembly Committee Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704143094 Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On separate occasions yesterday [19 April], 
Governor Ruan Chongwu and provincial people's congress Chairman 
Du Qinglin met a friendly visiting 6-member delegation of the 
Commercial and Industrial Resources Committee of the ROK 
National Assembly, led by committee Chairman An Tong Saeng. The 
delegation was visiting our province at the invitation of the 
provincial people's congress. 
  Ruan Chongwu and Du Qinglin separately briefed the guests on 
our province's investment environment and on other provinces' 
investments in the island, and hoped that both sides would 
conduct more friendly exchanges and develop cooperative 
projects. An Tong Saeing said that Hainan was a place full of 
vitality, and expressed his hope to develop undertakings in 
Hainan. 
  In attendance at the meetings were Wei Zefang, vice chairman 
of the provincial people's congress standing committee, and Mao 
Ping, secretary general of the provincial people's congress, as 
well as those in charge of relevant departments. 

</TEXT>

