<H3> <TI>   Hainan Secretary Meets Foreign Businessmen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hainan Secretary Meets Foreign Businessmen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704150294 Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Haikou Hainan People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary from poor reception] Ruan Chongwu expressed a 
welcome to Philippine banker (Chen Yung-cai) for his coming to 
Hainan on a fact-finding mission. Ruan briefed his guest on 
Hainan's investment environment and preferential policies. Both 
sides went on to express their intentions to develop projects in 
Hainan. Also present at the meeting were Mao Zhijun, director 
of the provincial economic cooperation department, as well as 
the director of the Hainan Provincial Civil Aviation Company. 
(Chen Yung-cai) and his party came to Hainan to study and 
discuss investment projects at the invitation of the Hainan 
Provincial Civil Aviation Company. 
  On 18 April, Ruan Chongwu, secretary of the Hainan 
Provincial 
CPC Committee and governor, met Kwok Chih-yi, general manager 
and member of the Board of Directors of Hong Kong's Wing On 
Department Store, and his party. The department store is an old 
establishment, with a long history in Hong Kong's general 
merchandise business. At the meeting, Governor Ruan Chongwu 
welcomed the department store's getting involved in Hainan's 
general retail merchandise business, and he briefed the party on 
Hainan's investment environment. Mr Kowk said that Haikou's 
general retail merchandise business has brights prospects. 

</TEXT>

