<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hunan Inaugurates First Share-Holding Technological </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hunan Inaugurates First Share-Holding Technological </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Enterprise 

<F P=102>   HK2804102994 Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2804102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Changsha Hunan People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Our province's first share-holding science and 
technology enterprise--Hunan Haili Chemical Industrial Company 
Limited--was officially founded in Changsha today. 
  Gu Xiulian, member of the CPC Central Committee and minister 
of chemical industry; He Guoqiang, vice minister of chemical 
industry; Wang Maolin, secretary of the Hunan Provincial CPC 
Committee; Governor Chen Bangzhu, deputy secretary of the 
provincial party committee; Liu Fusheng, chairman of the 
provincial people's congress standing committee; Liu Zheng, 
chairman of the Hunan Provincial Committee of the Chinese 
People's Political Consultative Conference; and other provincial 
party and government leaders; gladly wrote inscriptions to 
express their congratulations on the founding of the company. 
  Starting reform 10 years ago, the Hunan Chemical Industry 
Research Institute has been following the road of integrating 
science, industry, and trade. The institute has managed to 
increase its economic returns at an annual growth rate of 35 
percent. Its output value last year exceeded 100 million yuan. 
In order to advance on the overseas market, to apply the 
institute's scientific and technological research achievements 
to industrial production, and to present them to the overseas 
market as commodities, the Hunan Haili Chemical Industrial 
Company Limited--the province's first share-holding science and 
technology enterprise--was established, with the approval of the 
provincial commission for restructuring economic systems. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

