<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing To Carry Out Family Guidance Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing To Carry Out Family Guidance Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704144594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0919 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 27 (XINHUA)--A "family guidance 
program" jointly sponsored by Beijing Municipal Education 
Bureau, Beijing Federation of Women and Beijing Family Education 
Society is to be carried out in Beijing. 
  An official in charge of the program said that the aim is to 
enhance family education and improve the quality of the 
education. 
  The program will reach its climax on May 15 to mark the 
"International Family Day" which has been set by the United 
Nations. 
  Beijing has about 2.35 million children aged under 14 years. 
  Experts said that it is an important task to undertake 
family 
education among them. 
  The program will help parents to learn the physiological and 
psychological characteristics of children under the age of 14, 
and to master scientific education methods to answer children's 
questions in their growing-up process. 
  The program will also promote the idea of families improving 
their structure and becoming a favorable environment for the 
sake of children's healthy growth. 
  The program will run training schools for parents in 
communities, get special articles and programs put out in the 
media, publish books and open consultancy services to improve 
family education. 
  Beijing has now set up thousands of "schools for parents," 
and also has two special newspapers on family education. 
  In 1980, Beijing Family Education Society was set up and in 
1984, the city set up a Family Education Consultancy Center 
which has received 15,500 visits and 4,000 phone calls from 
parents. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
