<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tianjin Sets Up Rare-Earth Export Center </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tianjin Sets Up Rare-Earth Export Center </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604135794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1045 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, April 26 (XINHUA)--The first phase of 
construction of a rare-earth export center is expected to be 
completed in Tianjin port shortly. 
  Funded by Baotou Steel and the Rare Earth Corporation of the 
Baotou Iron and Steel Company, the project will turn Tianjin 
Port into the largest Chinese port to export rare-earth. 
  Three workshops and two warehouses, plus an office building, 
have already been constructed in the free trade zone near 
Tianjin Port. 
  The center will deal with all export and transport business 
of the Baotou Iron and Steel Company. 
  With the largest proportion of the deposits of rare-earth in 
the country, Baotou Iron and Steel Company in the Inner Mongolia 
Autonomous Region, exports large amounts of rare earth every 
year. 
  In 1992, the company decided to invest 30 million yuan in 
Tianjin's free trade zone to set up an industry and trade 
corporation of Baotou Iron and Steel Company, which is in charge 
of the construction of the center. 
  Huang Jianhua, deputy manager of the newly-established 
corporation, said that during the construction period, the 
corporation has exported rare-earth whose value was more than 6 
million U.S. dollars. 
  He said that by the end of 1995, about 60 million tons of 
rare- earth will have been exported to other countries through 
the center. 
  He said that his corporation will import equipment worth 170 
million U.S. dollars through the center. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

