<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing Says `Some' Taiwan People Exploit Boat Incident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Lanqing Says `Some' Taiwan People Exploit Boat Incident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704105294 Shanghai People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
2300 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2704105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanghai People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed station "special dispatch"; from the "Morning </F>
News" program] 
  [Text] Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing said on 26 April 
that the Chinese Government will draw a lesson from the recent 
Qiandao Hu incident, and will intensify crackdown on crime and 
strengthen the management of social order. 
  Li Lanqing made the above remark when meeting and discussing 
tourism industry with An Tong-son, chairman of the Committees on 
Commerce, Industry, and Resources of the Republic of Korea 
National Assembly. 
  He said: The Qiandao Hu case was a chance occurrence. This 
criminal case has been solved. 
  He expressed regrets and pains over the occurrence of the 
incident. However, he believed that some people in Taiwan are 
exploiting it to stir up a hue and cry and to pursue ulterior 
motives. 
  He said the incident will have little effect on China's 
tourism industry, adding that overall the safety rate of 
sightseeing in China is relatively high as compared with other 
countries in the world. 

</TEXT>

