<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sichuan To Sell Unprofitable State Enterprises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sichuan To Sell Unprofitable State Enterprises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704150494 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 1030 
GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chengdu, 14 April (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--The 
Sichuan Provincial Government recently decided to sell some 
state-owned enterprises suffering serious deficits to legal 
persons in China and overseas in a planned way. 
  The Sichuan Provincial State-Owned Assets Administration and 
Finance Office is encouraging enterprises to dispose of assets 
in various categories that are no longer applicable for use or 
indispensable, while giving permission to sell some workshops or 
factory branches with an unreasonable product mix and poor 
economic results, as well as some state-owned enterprises 
suffering serious deficits. 
  It is stipulated that before state-owned assets are sold, 
they must be assessed by an asset-appraisal organization, which 
will set a base price for the sale to a legal person; 
alternatively, their sale must be reported to state-owned asset 
departments at the same level and gain their consent. 

</TEXT>

