<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Notes Christopher-Kozyrev Talks on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Notes Christopher-Kozyrev Talks on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704035294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0309 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704035294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Russian Foreign Affairs 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev said here today that the Bosnian issue 
could be solved only by political means. 
  Kozyrev made these remarks at a joint press conference after 
meeting with U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher in the 
U.S. mission in Geneva. 
  According to Kozyrev, a military solution to the Bosnian 
conflict is an extreme solution which should not be used. 
  He also said that the warring sides in Bosnia should search 
for a compromise within the framework of negotiations over 
territorial concession by the Bosnian Serbs. 
  On economic sanctions against the Serbs, Kozyrev said this 
issue is linked to the search for a political solution, adding 
that lifting of the sanctions will be put on the agenda if a 
cease-fire is concluded. 
  Christopher said the U.S. and Russia have the same 
objectives 
in Bosnia. 
  On the situation in Goradze, the U.S. secretary of state 
said 
things are developing in a "good direction" and the Bosnian 
Serbs are withdrawing their heavy weapons some 20 kilometers 
away from the town. 
  However, Christopher added that NATO planes will monitor 
Serb 
compliance with the withdrawal. 
  Kozyrev and Christopher also discussed the Middle East, the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea, and Russian participation 
in NATO's partnership for peace plan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

