<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Peng Arrives in Mongolia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Peng Arrives in Mongolia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804095694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0951 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804095694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 28 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li 
Peng arrived here this afternoon for a two-day official visit, 
the first by a Chinese head of government to Mongolia in over 
three decades. 
  Prime Minister P. Jasray presided over a grand ceremony at 
the airport to welcome Li Peng, who ended a 10-day tour of 
Central Asia earlier today. 
  A written statement was issued upon Li's arrival at the 
airport. 
  "We are happy to see the gratifying expansion of 
Sino-Mongolian friendly cooperation in all fields in the past 
few years," Li said. 
  The maintaining of a friendly and good-neighborly 
relationship between China and Mongolia conforms with the common 
wishes and fundamental interests of the two peoples, and will 
benefit peace, stability and development in the Asia-Pacific 
region as well, he said. 
  During this visit, Li said, he expects to hold talks with 
Prime Minister P. Jasray and meet with president P. Ochirbat 
to exchange views on ways of furthering bilateral relations and 
on other issues of common concern. 
  Also, the two sides will sign a treaty on Sino-Mongolian 
friendship and cooperation, he said. 
  The document will further advance the friendly relations as 
well as exchanges and cooperation between the two countries in 
all fields, he said. 
  China will work together with Mongolia towards that goal, he 
said. 

</TEXT>

