<H3> <TI>   Deng Xiaoping in `Intensive Care' at Military Hospital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deng Xiaoping in `Intensive Care' at Military Hospital </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    In `Critical Condition' </H4>

<F P=102> OW2704042594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0359 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704042594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, April 27 KYODO -- China's paramount leader 
Deng Xiaoping is in intensive care at a military hospital 
following a sudden deterioration of health, a Seoul daily 
reported Wednesday [27 April]. 
  The SEGYE TIMES [SEGYE ILBO] in a dispatch from Beijing 
quoted Western sources as saying that Deng, who will turn 90 in 
August, has been hospitalized and is in critical condition. 
  The newspaper said in a front-page story that rumors are 
circulating in Beijing about Deng's worsening health, and 
possible death. 
  An official at the Foreign Ministry's [country not further 
identified] Northeast Asia Bureau reached by phone dismissed the 
report as totally groundless. 

</TEXT>

