BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 27 KYODO -- China on Wednesday [27 
April] denied a foreign report that paramount leader Deng 
Xiaoping is in intensive care at a military hospital. 
  A Foreign Ministry official said the report is a complete 
fabrication. "Comrade Deng is in very good heath," said the 
official who declined to be identified. 
  South Korea's SEGYE TIMES [SEGYE ILBO] reported Wednesday 
that Deng has been hospitalized and is in critical condition. 
  The Seoul daily said in a front-page story that rumors are 
circulating in Beijing about Deng's worsening health, and 
possible death. 

