<F P=100> Military </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liu Huaqing Urges Commanders To Study Deng Works </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liu Huaqing Urges Commanders To Study Deng Works </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704133594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1036 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2704133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 27 Apr (XINHUA) -- On the afternoon of 26 
April, Liu Huaqing, Standing Committee member of the CPC Central 
Committee Political Bureau and vice chairman of the Central 
Military Commission [CMC], attended a discussion with six 
military region [MR] commanders and political commissars, who 
were attending the third theoretical study class sponsored by 
the Central Party School for principal provincial and 
ministerial leading cadres. They discussed ways to deepen the 
study of Volume 3 of the "Selelected Works of Deng Xiaoping" and 
to use Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with 
Chinese characteristics and his concept of Army building in the 
new period to guide Army building in all fields. 
  CMC members Zhang Wannian, Yu Yongbo, and Fu Quanyou were 
present at the discussion. 
  At the discussion, MR leaders Li Xinliang, Liu Jingsong, 
Song 
Qingwei, Gu Hui, Li Xilin, and Li Jiulong spoke glowingly of 
their understandings gained from the intensive study of Volume 3 
of the "Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping" during a concentrated 
period of nearly 20 days. According to them, the more they 
studied the works, the deeper they realized the profound meaning 
and broad coverage of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics, as well as the great 
importance of studying Volume 3 of the "Selected Works of Deng 
Xiaoping," especially in the light of the realities in the 
Army's leadership work. As senior leading cadres, the MR 
leaders pledged to diligently study and master this theoretical 
weapon and use it to guide Army building. 
  Liu Huaqing said: To diligently study Volume 3 of the 
Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping and to use Comrade 
Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics to arm the minds of all Army commanders and 
fighters is the long-term strategic task of the whole Army, 
which must be carried out without fail. He emphasized: In 
studying Volume 3 of the Selected Works of Deng 
Xiaoping and correctly handling the relationship between 
reform, development, and stability and between local and 
national interests, it is imperative to integrate theory with 
practice. Senior cadres, in particular, should conscientiously 
set a good example for rank- and-file soldiers by promoting the 
Army's work in all fields and making positive contributions to 
China's reform, opening up, and modernization drive and to the 
maintenance of social stability. We should continue to educate 
all Army commanders and fighters to bring the Army's fine 
traditions into play and to preserve Red Army veterans' true 
color. We should administer the Army strictly. Cadres at all 
level must go deep into the realities to strengthen military 
training and ensure a good job in ideological and political 
work. At present, particular attention must be paid to managing 
troops and strengthening unity between the Army and the 
government and between armymen and civilians. 
  Xu Huizi, deputy chief of general staff, and Tang Tianbiao, 
assistant to the director of the General Political Department, 
also attended the discussion. 

</TEXT>

