<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anhui Blast Furnace Begins Operation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anhui Blast Furnace Begins Operation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704035794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0305 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704035794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 27 (XINHUA)--A 2,500-cu-m [cubic 
meter] blast furnace went into operation Tuesday [26 April] 
afternoon at the Maanshan Iron and Steel Co. Ltd, one of the 
country's major iron and steel producers, in east China's Anhui 
Province. 
  At 3:18 P.M. on Tuesday, the furnace successfully produced 
molten iron. 
  The total investment in the furnace reached three billion 
yuan (about 345 million U.S. dollars). 
  The designed annual output of the furnace is 1.75 million 
tons. With this furnace in production, the company will be able 
to double its annual output to four million tons of iron and 
steel. This also paves the way for it to increase its annual 
output to six million tons of iron and steel. 

</TEXT>

