<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong's Xie Fei on Rural Joint-Stock System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangdong's Xie Fei on Rural Joint-Stock System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2604133494 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 0400 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2604133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The provincial party committee held a forum in 
Nanhai City from 18 to 19 April on rural joint-stock cooperative 
system reform in the Zhu Jiang delta. Xie Fei, member of the 
Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and secretary of 
the Guangdong provincial party committee, presided over the 
forum and delivered the concluding speech. 
  The forum mainly discussed the issue of using the 
joint-stock 
cooperative system for land development that is evolving in 
relatively rich rural areas of the Zhu Jiang delta. The 
participants conscientiously discussed the important 
significance, basic requirements, guiding ideas, working 
principles, and policies of the reform. 
  Participants held that reforms related to the joint-stock 
cooperative system for land development which have been 
initiated in the developed areas of the Zhu Jiang delta are 
worth being introduced into other localities in the delta with a 
relatively developed economy and where there is a large, 
redundant rural labor force available, where secondary and 
tertiary industries, especially township and town enterprises, 
account for a great portion of the economy, and where the system 
is readily accepted by the peasants. It is necessary to 
gradually implement this system under strong leadership on the 
basis of pilot projects and in accordance with the principle 
that reform should give full play to the peasants' initiative 
and help to stabilize and promote agricultural production, 
promote economic returns, and increase peasants' incomes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

