<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing Releases Rice Reserves To Ease `Tense' Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Beijing Releases Rice Reserves To Ease `Tense' Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2804105194 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0736 GMT 
28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2804105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 28 (CNS)--In order to ease the tense 
state of the rice supply to residents in Beijing, the municipal 
grain administration has decided to put 10 million kilograms of 
rice onto the market in the capital. 
  It is reported that the main reasons for the rice shortage 
in 
the city are first, most of the grain shops there have been 
leased out and they are being used for selling other commodities 
while those with grain storage are refusing to sell grain to 
urban dwellers. Second, the fair markets there are either short 
of a rice supply or the prices of rice in such markets are too 
high or their quality is too low. In addition, some rice shops 
are running at a loss because the rice they sell is shipped from 
their original places of production resulting in the rice retail 
price being much higher than the price limitation set by the 
state with the highest price set at RMB 1.7 [renminbi] per 
kilogram. 
  The municipal grain bureau has allocated 10 million 
kilograms 
of rice to the state-run grain shops with the highest price set 
at RMB 1.6 per kilogram. 

</TEXT>

