<H3> <TI>   DPRK Proposes New Peace Agreement With U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Proposes New Peace Agreement With U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804205794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1854 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804205794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, April 28 (XINHUA) -- The Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) on Thursday [28 April] 
proposed that a new peace agreement be made with the U.S. to 
replace a 40-year old armistice agreement. 
  The proposal was declared by Pak Kil-yon, DPRK permanent 
representative to the UN, when reading out an official statement 
of the DPRK Foreign Ministry. 
  The statement said the recent move by the U.S. to ship 
"Patriot" missiles and a squadron of "Apache" helicopters 
constitute severe violation of the Korean armistice, which 
required non-introduction of any operational material from 
abroad and cessation of arms buildup on the Korean peninsula. 
  "Now that they have failed to live up to their 
responsibility 
for stabilizing the situation on the Korean peninsula and 
curbing military buildup there and they have been used for 
covering up the United States' policy of strangling DPRK," the 
statement said, "there is an absolute necessity for establishing 
a peace arrangment." 
  The statement added that such a new agreement could "prevent 
arms buildup or recurrence of war, stabilize the situation and 
reliably guarantee durable peace and security on the Korean 
peninsula on a practical basis." It called on the UN to respond 
to the proposal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

