<H3> <TI>   UN Chief Hopes Serbs Will Withdraw by Deadline </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Chief Hopes Serbs Will Withdraw by Deadline </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604225594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1947 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604225594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, April 26 (XINHUA) -- 
Secretary-General Butrus Butrus-Ghali today reiterated U.N.'s 
determination to use NATO air strikes against Bosnian Serb 
Forces if they do not withdraw from Gorazde by midnight. 
  "I am hoping that the Serbs will comply with the different 
resolutions which have been adopted by the United Nations (and 
NATO) and that they will withdraw from Gorazde to a perimeter of 
20 kilometers, and that we will not be compelled to use air 
strikes tonight at 8 o'clock New York time," said the 
secretary-general in a press conference in Bridgetown, Barbados 
today. 
  "But if they will not withdraw... [ellipses as received]," 
said the secretary-general, "Then we will use air strikes 
against them without any hesitation," according to a U.N. news 
release today. 
  The NATO April-22 decision said all Bosnian Serb heavy 
weapons must be withdrawn by 0001 GMT on April 27 (0800 New York 
time). Otherwise, "These weapons and other Bosnian Serb military 
assets, as well as their direct and essential military support 
facilities, including but not limited to fuel installations and 
munitions sites, will be subject to NATO air strikes." 

</TEXT>

