<H3> <TI>   Attends Nixon's Funeral </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Attends Nixon's Funeral </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2904000394 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0821 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2904000394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 28 (XINHUA) -- Ending his official 
visit to Canada on 27 April, Chinese Vice Premier Zou Jiahua 
made a special trip to California, United States, Yorba Linda 
City to attend former U.S. President Nixon's funeral on behalf 
of the Chinese Government. 
  Zou Jiahua presented a wreath at Nixon's coffin with 
characters written on the attached satin strap that read "We 
Deeply Mourn Mr. Richard Nixon [shen qie dao nian li cha de ni 
ke song xian sheng 3234 0434 1902 1819 3810 2686 1795 1441 0344 
2646 0341 3932]." Expressing his heartfelt condolences over 
Nixon's death at the funeral, Zou Jiahua said: Nixon is an old 
friend of the Chinese people; we will never forget the positive 
efforts and contributions he made in establishing and developing 
Sino-American relations. 
  Vice Foreign Minister Liu Huaqiu and Chinese Ambassador to 
the United States Li Daoyu also attended the funeral. 

</TEXT>

