<F P=100> Central Eurasia </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Notes Signing of Russia's Civic Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Notes Signing of Russia's Civic Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804122994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1148 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, April 28 (XINHUA) -- Russia's civic accord, 
which is aimed at stabilizing the political and economic 
situation in the country, was singed here in the Kremlin today. 
  Present at the signing ceremony were President Boris 
Yeltsin, 
Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, speakers of the two houses 
Ivan Rybkin and Vladimir Shumeyko, and political parties' 
leaders and leaders of the republics and regions. 
  The document was proposed by Yeltsin soon after his main 
opponents, including former Vice-President Aleksander Rutskoy 
and former parliament speaker Ruslan Khasbulatov, were freed in 
late February by the State Duma's political amnesty. 
  More than 100 participants of the ceremony signed the 
document, which will remain valid for two years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

