<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Notes Intensification of Conflict in Cambodia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Notes Intensification of Conflict in Cambodia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2804120794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0834 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2804120794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh, April 28 (XINHUA) -- Military conflict 
between Cambodian Government troops and Khmer Rouge guerrillas 
is spreading from Pailin to Poipet, a senior officer of the 
Defense Ministry said here today. 
  He said that government troops were fighting Khmer Rouge 
guerrillas in Poipet, an important Cambodian-thai border town in 
the west of Battambang Province, in the past few days. The 
Khmer Rouge started an offensive against the government troops 
on April 26, he added, but disclosing no details. 
  A representative of the Khmer Rouge said here yesterday that 
after the recapture of Pailin on April 19, their guerrillas have 
pushed the fighting toward an area about 30 kilometers from 
Battambang. 
  Broadcasts of Khmer Rouge radio monitored here today also 
said that the guerrillas took over the headquarters of the 4th 
division of the government troops in Treng, along road No. 10 
yesterday morning. 
  There is no signs of a cease-fire from the two warring 
sides, 
although all parties have responded positively to the King 
Norodom Sihanouk in favor of a roundtable meeting on peace and 
national reconciliation, scheduled for May 2-7 in Phnom Penh. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

