<H3> <TI>   Malaysian Prime Minister Meets Fujian Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Malaysian Prime Minister Meets Fujian Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704140194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1305 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Malaysian Prime 
Minister Mahathir Mohamed met with Jia Qinglin, chairman of the 
Standing Committee of the People's Congress of Fujian Province, 
China, here today. 
  In a friendly and cordial conversation, Mahathir expressed 
his hope that the Fuzhou-Quanzhou highway project under the 
cooperation between Fujian Province and two groups of investors 
of Malaysia will be a success. The experience from the project 
can promote friendship and cooperation between the two 
countries, he said. 
  Jia thanked Mahathir for his care and support for the 
project. He also briefed the Malaysian leader on Fujian Province 
and its success in carrying out the economic reform. 
  Jia Qinglin arrived here on Saturday. During his stay, he 
has called on several ministers of Malaysia and met with 
Malaysian businessmen to discuss economic cooperation between 
Fujian and Malaysia. 

</TEXT>

