<H3> <TI>   Australian Governor General Visits Xinjiang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Australian Governor General Visits Xinjiang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2504212894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1545 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2504212894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Urumqi, April 25 (XINHUA) -- Australian 
Governor-General Bill Hayden concluded his five-day visit to the 
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region here today and left here by 
special plane this morning for Xiamen. 
  Hayden told reporters at the airport that his visit to 
Xinjiang enhanced his understanding of the great achievement of 
China's economic development. 
  Accompanied by chairman of the Chinese Government reception 
commission and Vice-Minister in Charge of the State Economic and 
Trade Commission Yu Xiaosong, Hayden and his party arrived here 
on April 21 from Beijing. 
  Hayden and his party visited Urumqi, Kashgar and Turpan and 
gained more knowledge about Xinjiang's economic development, 
folklore, and the development of cooperative projects between 
Australia and Xinjiang. 
  The Australian guests said that their visit to Xinjiang has 
left a deep impression on their minds. 

</TEXT>

