<H3> <TI>   Australian Governor General Visits Xinjiang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Australian Governor General Visits Xinjiang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704110794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1354 
GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2704110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporterd Li Shengjiang (2621 3932 3068)] </F>
  [Text] Urumqi, 25 Apr (XINHUA) -- Australian Governor 
General William Hayden wound up a five-day visit to Xinjiang and 
left Urumqi for Xiamen by special plane this morning. 
  Hayden told reporters at the airport that the visit to 
Xinjiang has deepened his impressions of China's remarkable 
economic achievements. 
  Accompanied by Yu Xiaosong, head of the Chinese Government 
Reception Committee and vice minister in charge of the State 
Economic and Trade Commission, Hayden and his retinue arrived in 
Urumqi from Beijing on 21 April. While in Xinjiang, the 
Australian Governor General visited Urumqi, Kashi, and Turpan to 
obtain firsthand information about Xinjiang's economic 
development, ethnic habits and customs, and economic, trade, and 
scientific and technical exchange and cooperation with Australia. 
  The Australian visitors were very much impressed with their 
visit to Xinjiang. 
  Abulaiti Abudurexiti, chairman of Xinjiang Uigur Autonomous 
Region, met and feted Hayden and his retinue, and extended a 
warm welcome to the Australian visitors. 

</TEXT>

