<H3> <TI>   Chen Junsheng, Delegation Arrive in Morocco 24 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chen Junsheng, Delegation Arrive in Morocco 24 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704234794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0502 
GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2704234794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rabat, 24 Apr (XINHUA) -- A Chinese Government 
agricultural delegation, led by State Councilor Chen Junsheng, 
arrived here today for a four-day visit to Morocco. 
  The Chinese delegation was welcomed at the airport by 
Mustapha Sahil, Moroccan minister of fisheries and merchant 
marine, and other officials as well as Chinese ambassador to 
Morocco An Guozheng. 
  Speaking to the press at the airport, Chen Junsheng said: 
This visit is to strengthen Sino-Moroccan friendly and 
cooperative relations, particularly in agriculture and the 
fishing industry. 
  During the visit, Chen Junsheng will hold talks with 
Moroccan 
leaders on issues of common interest. 

</TEXT>

