<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chen Junsheng Arrives in Mauritania, Meets With Taya </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chen Junsheng Arrives in Mauritania, Meets With Taya </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2904030994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0220 GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2904030994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nouakchott, April 28 (XINHUA) -- Mauritanian 
President Maaouiya Ould Sid'Ahmed Taya and visiting Chinese 
State Councillor Chen Junsheng expressed here today their hope 
to enhance cooperation between the two nations in fisheries and 
agriculture. 
  Chen, who is leading a Chinese delegation to pay a four-day 
visit to Mauritania, met with President Taya this afternoon. 
  Chen said Mauritania is China's reliable friend, and he 
expressed thanks to Taya for support in international affairs 
such as China's return to GATT (General Agreement on Tariffs and 
Trade) and the issue of human rights. 
  The Chinese state councillor, who just arrived here today, 
said that one of the goals of his visit was to promote all-round 
cooperation between the two countries, especially in agriculture 
and fisheries. 
  President Taya said that the two countries have a long 
history of friendship and cooperation and he believed that such 
friendship and cooperation would be further developed. 
  He highly appreciated China's achievements in agriculture 
and 
industry and said that his nation was willing to cooperate with 
China in fisheries and agriculture. 

</TEXT>

