<H3> <TI>   Nepal Parliamentary Delegation Arrives in Xian </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nepal Parliamentary Delegation Arrives in Xian </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2704145394 Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network in Mandarin 
0010 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2704145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Xian Shaanxi People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] (Karki Shah), chairman of Nepal's National Council, 
and his wife and party, who are currently on a visit to China at 
the invitation of the National Committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference [CPPCC], arrived in Xian on 13 
April for sightseeing and a visit. 
  Zhou Yaguang, chairman of the CPPCC provincial committee, 
met 
and feted Chairman (Karki) and his wife and party at the Xian 
Guest House yesterday evening. Chairman Zhou briefed the guests 
on Shaanxi's long cultural history, its natural resources, and 
its achievements in economic construction since the drive for 
reform and opening up to the outside world was launched. He 
hoped that China and Nepal would conduct more frequent contacts 
in the days to come so as to promote understanding, and wished 
that the chairman's current visit to Xian would help deepen 
cooperation between Shaanxi and Nepal. 
  Chairman (Karki) said: The unbreakable friendship between 
China and Nepal has lasted for several thousand years. China's 
aid to Nepal is there for all to see. The Nepalese people 
cherish deep feelings for China. He expressed his belief that 
the friendship between the two countries would last for 
generation after generation. 
  During their stay in Xian, Chairman (Karki) and his party 
visited scenic spots and historical sites, such as the site of 
the terra- cotta warriors and horses of the Qing Dynasty, the 
(Dayan) Temple, and the Xian Satellite Control Center. 

</TEXT>

