<H3> <TI>   More on Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2904111094 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0802 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2904111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporters Bata Ercang (1572 1044 1422 0221) and Chang </F>
Wanlong (1603 8001 7127)] 
  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, 29 Apr (XINHUA) -- Premier Li Peng met 
with chairman (Speaker) Natsagiyn Bagabandi of Mongolia's Great 
Hural and had a friendly conversation with him this morning. 
  Li Peng first conveyed the regards of Qiao Shi, National 
People's Congress [NPC] Standing Committee chairman, to 
Bagabandi and then the NPC's hope for strengthened cooperation 
with Mongolia's parliament. 
  Bagabandi expressed his thanks for this hope. He said: 
Relations between the two countries are developing smoothly 
thanks to the concerted efforts by both sides. We are satisfied 
with the progress. Premier Li Peng's official visit to Mongolia 
is a historic visit and is of great significance for pushing 
bilateral ties to a new stage. The Mongolian parliament 
approves of the two governments' policies of developing 
bilateral friendly cooperation. He spoke highly of the 
Mongolian-Chinese treaty of friendly relations and cooperation 
to be signed soon, and he said that the signing of this treaty 
will lay a good legal foundation for the further expansion of 
bilateral ties. 
  Bagabandi said: The exchanges between the two parliaments 
play an important role in developing relations between the two 
countries. At present, cooperation between the two parliaments 
has been fully normalized, and exchanges have been increasing 
year after year. A delegation of the Mongolian Great Hural will 
pay an official visit to China in August in the hope of learning 
about China's reform and opening, as well as about the work of 
the NPC. 
  Li Peng said he was very much satisfied with the fruitful 
results of his visit to Mongolia. The signing of the bilateral 
treaty of friendly relations and cooperation will turn a new 
page in bilateral ties and will promote the advancement of 
bilateral ties in all spheres. The Chinese Government will 
continue working toward that goal. 
  Li Peng said: China's NPC and Mongolia's Great Hural 
shoulder an important responsibility for furthering friendship 
between the peoples of the two countries and for expanding 
bilateral friendly cooperation. We are happy to see that 
relations between the two parliaments have been developing well 
in recent years. 
  Premier Li Peng also briefed the other side on China's 
domestic situation, reform, and opening to the outside world, as 
well as on its efforts to improve its legal system. 

</TEXT>

