<F P=106> [By reporter Bata Ercang (1572 1044 1422 0221)] </F>
  [Text] Ulaabaatar, 29 Apr (XINHUA) -- After holding talks 
at the State Palace, visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng and 
Mongolian Prime Minister P. Jasray told the press on the morning 
of 29 April that they highly appraised the results of the talks 
and the Sino- Mongolian Treaty of Friendly Relations and 
Cooperation to be signed soon. 
  The two premiers agreed that the talks proceeded in a 
friendly and cordial atmosphere. Both sides exchanged views on 
bilateral relations and on international issues of common 
interest. When the late Premier Zhou Enlai visited Mongolia 34 
years ago, he concluded the Sino-Mongolian Friendship and Mutual 
Aid Treaty. The new Sino- Mongolian Treaty of Friendly 
Relations and Cooperation to be signed soon will lay the legal 
foundation for bilateral relations. Both sides will also sign a 
series of bilateral documents on specific cooperation issues. 
The talks were fruitful. 

