<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 26 (XINHUA) -- A party workers' 
delegation from the Communist Party of China (CPC) left here 
this afternoon on a visit to the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea (DPRK). 
  The delegation, which is led by Bai Keming, deputy head of 
the Propaganda Department of the CPC Central Committee, is 
paying the visit at the invitation of the International 
Department of the Workers' Party of Korea. 

