<H3> <TI>   Li Lanqing Meets ROK Visitors 26 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Lanqing Meets ROK Visitors 26 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604125594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1136 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
Li Lanqing met with Dong-seon An [spelling of name as received], 
chairman of the Committee on Commerce, Industry and Resources of 
the National Assembly of the Republic of Korea (ROK), and his 
party here today. 
  Dong-seon an and his party arrived here April 24 as guests 
of 
the Finance and Economic Committee of China's National People 
Congress (NPC). 
  Prior to their arrival in Beijing, the visitors had toured 
south China's Hainan Province and Harbin in Heilongjiang 
Province, northeast China. 
  During the meeting this afternoon, Vice-Premier Li said that 
the current visit will promote bilateral cooperation in trade 
and tourism. 
  ROK President Kim Yong-sam's recent China visit has played 
an 
important role in pushing forward the friendly relations of 
cooperation between the two countries, Li said. 
  Dong-seon An expressed belief that bilateral cooperation in 
trade and tourism will see greater development through the joint 
efforts of the two governments. 
  Liu Suinian, chairman of the NPC Finance and Economic 
Committee, took part in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

