<F P=102>   SK2804134894 Beijing China Radio International in Korean 
1100 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2804134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing China Radio International </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Li Lanqing, vice premier of the Chinese State 
Council, met An Tong-sun, chairman of the Trade, Industry, and 
Resources Committee of the ROK National Assembly, and his 
entourage in Beijing on the afternoon of 26 April. Chairman An 
Tong-sun and his entourage arrived in Beijing for a visit to 
China on 24 April at the invitation of the Financial and 
Economic Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress. 
  Prior to this, the ROK guests visited Hainan Province and 
Harbin at the invitation of the Hainan and Heilongjiang 
Provinces. 
  At the meeting, Vice Premier Li Lanqing said that President 
Kim Yong-sam's visit to China, which was made sometime ago, has 
played an important initiative role in the development of the 
friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

