  [Text] Brasilia, April 26 (XINHUA) -- Senior Chinese 
Communist Party official Hu Jintao and Brazilian parliament 
leaders expressed their desire today to expand friendship and 
cooperation between the parliaments of the two countries. 
  Hu, member of the Standing Committee of the Politburo of the 
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, met with President of 
the Senate Humberto Lucena and President of the Chamber of 
Deputies Inocencio de Oliveira today respectively. 
  Lucena praised the China's success in the development of its 
economy, saying that China is an example to follow by developing 
countries for their economic development. 
  De Oliveira said he expects a bigger exchange between the 
legislative powers of China and Brazil. 
  Hu said that China accelerates its economic development, it 
perfects its juridical system. [sentence as received] China 
has started to implement programs for juridical construction, 
planned during the recent years. 
  Hu Jintao stressed that China and Brazil, two big countries 
of Asia and Latin America, should play roles in safeguarding 
peace and stability in the world and in the development and 
progress of mankind. 
  Hu and his delegation arrived in Brasilia last night at the 
invitation of the Brazilian Government. 

