<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statistics Show 300 Million Smokers in China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statistics Show 300 Million Smokers in China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2804022894 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1236 GMT 
27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2804022894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, April 27 (CNS)--According to the latest 
information from the Mainland authorities, China now has nearly 
300 million smokers, 30 million of them female. The annual 
consumption of over 150 billion cigarettes accounts for 30 
percent of the world's total. 
  Because many of them are closet smokers, the actual number 
of 
the female smokers may be much bigger. According to surveys, 33 
percent of female smokers said they smoked as a way of asserting 
their equality with men while 40 percent of them said they 
smoked because of the influence of other smokers. A middle 
school class in Beijing saw 32 percent of its students smoking 
because of fun. Other reasons for the bad habit by women 
include the failures in love, novelty-seeking and a way to kill 
time. 
  Women smoking in recent years has not only become a problem 
harmful to health but also an increasingly serious social 
problem, creating new obstacles for the anti-smoking campaign in 
the country. 

</TEXT>

