<H3> <TI>   Insurance Market Attracts Foreign Firms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Insurance Market Attracts Foreign Firms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2704115294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0707 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2704115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tianjin, April 27 (XINHUA) -- Over 40 overseas 
insurance companies had opened representative offices in China 
by the end of February this year, according to a spokesman for 
the People's Insurance Company of China (PICC). 
  He added that a U.S. company has been given permission to 
open a hard-currency insurance business in China. 
  Addressing the annual conference on overseas insurance 
business, which opened here this week, the deputy general 
manager of the picc's international department said his company 
made 732 million U.S. dollars-worth of premiums last year, an 
increase of 29.8 percent over the previous year, and paid out 
356 million U.S. dollars-worth in compensation, accounting for 
48.76 percent of the total premiums. 
  He told the conference that the PICC's overseas business now 
ranges from general insurance to some high-risk areas such as 
aeronautics, oil exploitation and construction of nuclear power 
stations. 
  He said all the fields available in the international market 
are covered by the PICC, among which property insurance for 
foreign-funded enterprises and insurance for short-term credit 
and the buyer's contract responsibility are the most popular. 
  So far, the PICC has established two regional companies in 
Hong Kong and Europe, respectively, and over 70 branches and 
offices worldwide. 

</TEXT>

