<H3> <TI>   Forum Discusses Navigation Problems at Three Gorges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Forum Discusses Navigation Problems at Three Gorges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2604134794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1101 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2604134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chongqing, April 26 (XINHUA) -- A forum was 
recently held in Chongqing to tackle navigation problems during 
the construction of the Three Gorges Dam on the Chang Jiang 
River. 
  Nearly 30 experts in hydropower and navigation took part in 
the forum, sponsored by the office of the Three Gorges project 
of the State Council and the Ministry of Communications. 
  Experts from the South-West Marine Transport Institute 
reported their latest research on the navigation channel, 
silting and other issues that have to be solved during the 
17-year construction of the dam. 
  The institute suggests that instead of building a temporary 
ship lock and a ship lift, vessels could pass through a channel 
during the construction. 
  The institute has since early 1992 been doing lab research. 

