<H3> <TI>   Shandong's Qingdao Opens Minerals Transfer Port </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shandong's Qingdao Opens Minerals Transfer Port </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2904102794 Jinan DAZHONG RIBAO in Chinese 20 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2904102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jinan DAZHONG RIBAO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] With a joint investment of 160 million yuan by the 
Qingdao Port Office and the ISCOY Corporation of the Republic of 
South Africa, the 100,000-tonne-class wharf specially for 
shipping minerals located at Qingdao Harbor's Qianwan area was 
formally made available to users on 16 April. Now, Qingdao 
Harbor has become the largest minerals transfer port in northern 
China. This wharf is primarily devoted to unloading, storing, 
and transferring minerals from South Africa. The annual 
comprehensive handling capacity is estimated at 6 million tonnes. 

</TEXT>

