<H3> <TI>   Further on Foreign Ministry's Weekly Briefing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Foreign Ministry's Weekly Briefing </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Views Sino-India Border Issue </H4>

<F P=102> OW2804112994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1100 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2804112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 28 Apr (XINHUA) -- Answering a reporter's 
question at a news conference this afternoon, a spokesman of the 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs pointed out that the report about 
China having sent additional troops to the Sino-India border is 
a "sheer fabrication" [chun shu nie zao 4783 1466 2250 6644]. 
  A reporter asked: According to a report, China recently sent 
additional 30,000 troops into Tibet and deployed them along the 
Sino-Indian border areas. Please confirm and comment. 
  The spokesman said: The report is sheer fabrication. Last 
year the Chinese and Indian Governments signed an accord on 
maintaining peace and tranquility in areas along the Line of 
Actual Control, and the two countries have also started 
discussing issues about reducing troops in areas along the line. 
Spreading the lie that China has sent an additional 30,000 
troops to the Sino-Indian border areas is obviously out of 
ulterior motives. 

</TEXT>

